  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen turning on dark mode in Status, the software navigation bar in the Android OS remains white.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen I enable Dark Mode, I expect the navigation bar to turn dark.\r\nWhen I enable System Mode and I have Dark System mode, I expect the navigation bar to turn dark.\r\nWhen I disable Dark Mode, I expect the navigation bar to turn light.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nWhen I enable Dark Mode, the navigation bar stays light.\r\nWhen I enable System Mode and I have Dark System mode, the navigation bar stays light.\r\nWhen I disable Dark Mode, the navigation bar stays light.\r\n\r\n#### Notes\r\n\r\nPossibly setting navigationBarColor and windowLightNavigationBar = false?\r\nhttps://developer.android.com/reference/android/R.attr#windowLightNavigationBar\r\nor setting the bar translucent. \r\n\r\n#### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nFollow steps to Reproduce, but instead of being blinded, enjoying the dark theme throughout the screen.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Have an Android phone with a software navigation bar\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Profile > Appearance > Choose Dark (or System)\r\n- Get blinded by bright navigation bar\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: 1.3.0\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n",
